  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Message counter layout is broken when there are more than 999 messages unread. 4 digits number is too large to show in this blue circle\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nMessage counter should not be broken. I suggest showing `99+` value when there are more than 99 messages, so we still stick to use 3 digits that are shown fine\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28752642/40045571-57e5825c-5833-11e8-8dfd-708ac89a3c09.png)\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Receive more than 999 messages in public/group chat\r\n- Pay attention  to unread counter\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS",
